Libraries

    pandas: A data manipulation library. The code uses it to read CSV files into DataFrames,
            effectively using them as a substitute for a traditional database to store hotel,
            credit card, and security information.

    abc: The Abstract Base Classes module. The code imports ABC and abstractmethod to create
            foundational blueprint classes that force child classes to follow a specific structure.

Classes

    Hotel: Represents a hotel property. It handles the initialization of hotel details,
            checks for room availability, and executes the booking process by modifying the external data source.

    CreditCard: Represents a standard credit card. It takes a card number upon creation and provides
                functionality to validate the card's expiration, CVC, and holder name against a dataset.

    SecurityCreditCard: A child class that inherits from CreditCard. It extends the base
                        functionality by adding a secondary authentication layer that checks a password.

    ReservationTicket: Represents a booking confirmation. It aggregates customer information and
                        a Hotel object to generate a formatted reservation receipt.

    SpaTicket: Similar to the reservation ticket, it represents an add-on service.
                It uses customer and hotel data to generate a specific spa confirmation receipt.

    Ticket: An abstract base class. It serves purely as a structural template, establishing the rule
            that any inheriting ticket class must possess a generation method.

    DigitalTicket: A child class inheriting from Ticket. It represents an electronic ticket
                    format and provides its own specific implementation for generating the ticket content.

Properties & Variables

    watermark (Class Variable): A string assigned directly to the Hotel class. It is a shared attribute,
                                meaning every hotel object created will possess this exact same value.

    the_customer_name (Property): Located in ReservationTicket. It is accessed like a variable but executes
                                    a method behind the scenes. It takes the raw customer name, strips away extra spaces,
                                     and capitalizes the first letters for clean formatting.

Magic Methods

    __init__ (Constructor): The initialization method triggered automatically when a new object is created.
                            The codebase uses it across multiple classes to assign initial values
                            (like IDs, names, or reference objects) to the newly formed instance.

    __eq__ (Equality Operator): Overrides how Python handles the == comparison. In the Hotel class,
                                it instructs the program to consider two completely different hotel objects
                                as "equal" as long as their hotel_id values match.

Methods

    book (Instance Method): Belongs to the Hotel class. It changes the specific hotel's availability
                            status to "no" within the DataFrame and immediately overwrites the physical
                            CSV file to lock in the reservation.

    available (Instance Method): Belongs to the Hotel class. It queries the DataFrame to check if the
                                specific hotel's status is listed as "yes" and returns a True/False value accordingly.

    validate (Instance Method): Belongs to CreditCard. It packages the provided expiration date,
                                CVC, and holder name into a dictionary and checks if that exact combination
                                exists within the loaded credit card dataset.

    authenticate (Instance Method): Belongs to SecurityCreditCard. It locates the row matching
                                    the instance's card number in the security dataset and checks if the
                                     provided password matches the stored password.

    generate (Instance Method): Found in ReservationTicket, SpaTicket, and DigitalTicket. It constructs and
                                returns a formatted text block containing the final receipt details.

    generate (Abstract Method): Found in the Ticket class. It contains no code of its own (pass);
                                it exists solely to force any class inheriting from Ticket to create its own
                                functional version of the method.

    get_hotel_count (Class Method): Bound to the Hotel class itself rather than an instance. It accepts
                                    the class (cls) and a dataset, returning the total number of items in that dataset.

    convert (Static Method): Located in ReservationTicket. It acts as an independent utility function that
                            multiplies a given amount by 1.2. It requires no knowledge of the class or object state to execute.